But perhaps thatĺs where we need to begin, lets look at what Spam ę  really is. <br><br>
Spam ę is nothing less then degraded left over chopped up ham that has been forced into an odd looking but colorful red, white and blue can.  The cans used to come with their own can openers in the bottom because it was such an odd shaped can but heck they donĺt even provide them anymore. Instead new improved can openers made those keys worthless. Instead the system who would have looked at Spam in a round can as looking too much like canned dog meat, changed. Since Spam ę would not change the shape of its cans, the system instead provided a can opener capable of opening all types of weird shaped cans. <br>
 <br>
I see the anti-war movement as nothing less then Spam ę, the offspring of the counterculture movement. The immediate afterbirth accompanying a confused and wayward child. But the afterbirth and the offspring soon found themselves engaged in a feeding frenzy and both were soon indulging in all types of selfish denials, sexual perversion, drugs and destructive behavior. In post # 3 you mentioned,<br><br>
ôI believe that war creates strange bed fellows. When your life depends on a unity of action with someone<br>
you tend to overlook their ethnicity.ö <br><br>
Is this not what we found in the Anti-war movement? It was the strangest of all copulation. The Communist party with its various factions found itself side by side and embracing the hippies of the Age of Aquarius. The Quakers begin bedding down with idealistic socialists. The Weatherman with the Black Panther Party. The Students for a Democratic Society (SDS), with a number of other socialist as well as with racist individuals. All of them all of a sudden found themselves sharing the same bed and engaged in the same idealistic torments. Yet, each one of them were convinced of their OWN MORAL SUPERIORITY over each other and ESPECIALLY over those that went to war. They all knew best what was right for American, and all knew what the war was all about. But, in all that knowledge they found no wisdom in supporting any commitment to helping the South Vietnamese people. No wisdom in speaking out against but instead totally disregarded the atrocities being committed in South Vietnam by invading Communist trained soldiers. <br><br>
Where was all that knowledge about the war then, why was only one side selectively propagated? Was it because exposing the destructive force of Communist aggression not conducive to the one sided self-serving intrinsic behavior of the counter-culture and anti-war movement?<br><br>
Letĺs open up that can of Spam ę and what do we find? That each of these so called social reformers had their own private agenda that they were all blind to the need of supporting the American fighting men while they bled and died fighting for the South Vietnamese to have their own right to free speech. Instead the anti-war and counter culture movement continued their own self serving open copulation with the others in order to broader their own secret agendas. They could care less of the American fighting men or the people of South Vietnam, talk about dehumanization. Here it was all done for selfish self serving interest. <br><br>
The anti-war movement in America fed upon the counter culture revolution and visa versa and each used each other so that soon it became impossible to see which was which. The two became united in issuing their own license for destruction, for seduction, to riot, to scandalize, do use drugs, to participate in group sex, talk and dress dirty, to burn the American flag, to denounce their parents, the government, burn down government and large corporate businesses as well as condemn anyone over 30 years of age. One could not be involved in one aspect of those antiwar movements without participating in the others. <br><br>
The anti-war movement prolonged the war, it fed Presidents Johnson's political and cowardly stand while feeding McNamara's fear of commitment. It caused the lives of many American soldiers and destroyed American from within. That is what in the end the Anti-war movement accomplished. <br><br>
The anti-war movement gave birth to open hatred toward all military and government employees. The anti-war movement never stopped the war it only fed America's countercultureĺs agenda. Today we see the by-products of those days, it gave birth to Abortion on demand. To feminism, permissive sexuality and its by-products of AIDS and all other forms of destructive sexual diseases. To open gay and lesbian practices and a number of other degenerate practices that have brought nothing but shame upon America. <br><br>
The anti-war movement was just another vehicle, used to broaden the counter culture philosophies and secret agenda, and it was all crammed inside that same can of Spam ę. All of these movements turned this countryĺs proud heritage into a shameful disgrace. It destroyed our country's pride in its youth and the only real hope American has today can be found in the sons and in the daughters of those that were willing to fight, who were proud to serve their county who were NOT smart enough to stay out of the war. Gosh I wish I knew then what I know today.  <br><br>
But tell me Jeb what do you teach today? What counter culture, anti-American propaganda are you feeding Americas youth today?<br><br>
You said, ôTo those who went and feel guilty and to those who did not go and feel guilty... There is something wrong with this picture.ö Let me add to those involved in the Anti-war movement after seeing its aftermath today, to not too feel guilty today, there is something very, very wrong with that picture. It was after all once the can was fully open not even spam, it was dog meat in a very strange looking can. <br><br>
